.\" get.1 — manual page for get(1)
.\"
.\" Author:  WaterRun
.\" GitHub:  https://github.com/Water-Run/get
.\" License: AGPL-3.0
.\"
.TH GET 1 "2026-04-19" "get 1.0" "User Commands"
.\"
.\" ====================================================================
.SH NAME
get \- get anything from your computer
.\"
.\" ====================================================================
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B get
.RI \(dq query \(dq
.RI [ flags ]
.br
.B get set
.I option
.RI [ value ]
.br
.B get config
.RI [ \-\-reset | \-\- option ]
.br
.B get cache
.RI [ \-\-clean | "\-\-unset \(dq" query \(dq ]
.br
.B get log
.RI [ \-\-clean ]
.br
.B get get
.RI [ \-\-intro | \-\-version | \-\-license | \-\-github ]
.br
.B get version
.br
.B get isok
.br
.B get help
.\"
.\" ====================================================================
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B get
is a small command-line tool that uses a large language model (LLM) to
generate shell commands from natural-language queries and executes them
to retrieve information from your device.
It is designed to perform
.B read-only
operations only.
Every generated command passes through multiple safety layers before
execution.
.PP
.B get
is compatible with any OpenAI-API-compatible endpoint and ships with
bundled high-performance command-line tools
.RB ( rg ,
.BR fd ,
.BR sg ,
.BR pmc ,
.BR treepp / tree ,
.BR tokei ,
.BR lua ,
.BR bat ,
.BR mdcat )
that are automatically available to generated commands.
A lightweight edition without the bundled
.I bin/
directory is also available; in that case only system-installed tools
are used.
.PP
.B get
supports two execution modes:
.TP
.B Instance mode
A single LLM call produces one command whose output is shown directly
to the user.
Fast and suitable for simple queries.
Enabled via
.B "get set instance true"
or the
.B \-\-instance
flag.
.TP
.B Agent mode (default)
A multi-round loop in which the LLM can execute intermediate read-only
commands to gather information before producing a final answer.
Each response carries a protocol marker
.RB ( "<!-- CONTINUE -->" ,
.BR "<!-- FINAL -->" ,
or
.BR "<!-- INTERPRET -->" )
that determines whether execution continues or terminates.
A hard cap
.RB ( max-rounds ,
default 3) prevents unbounded loops.
.\"
.\" ====================================================================
.SH COMMANDS
.\"
.\" --------------------------------------------------------------------
.SS "Query (default)"
.BI "get \(dq" "query" "\(dq [" "flags" "]"
.PP
Sends
.I query
to the configured LLM, which generates one or more shell commands.
In agent mode the LLM may run intermediate commands before producing a
final answer; in instance mode a single command is generated and
executed immediately.
Every generated command is validated, optionally double-checked and
confirmed, then executed.
.PP
See
.B QUERY FLAGS
below for per-invocation overrides.
.\"
.\" --------------------------------------------------------------------
.SS set
.BI "get set " "option" " [" "value" "]"
.PP
Sets a single configuration option.
Omitting
.I value
resets the option to its default (for booleans and integers) or clears
it (for strings).
See
.B SET OPTIONS
for the full list.
.\"
.\" --------------------------------------------------------------------
.SS config
.B get config
.PP
Displays all current configuration values.
.TP
.B \-\-reset
Resets all configuration to default values and clears the stored API key.
.TP
.BI \-\- option
Displays the current value of a single option, where
.I option
is any name from the
.B SET OPTIONS
table (e.g.\&
.BR \-\-model ,
.BR \-\-timeout ).
The
.B \-\-key
flag shows the key status with the value masked.
.\"
.\" --------------------------------------------------------------------
.SS cache
.B get cache
.PP
Displays cache status: whether caching is enabled, total and per-mode
entry counts, configured limits, and file location.
.TP
.B \-\-clean
Removes all cached entries.
.TP
.BI "\-\-unset \(dq" query \(dq
Removes all cache entries whose query text matches
.I query
(case-insensitive).
.\"
.\" --------------------------------------------------------------------
.SS log
.B get log
.PP
Displays log status: whether logging is enabled, configured maximum
entries, entry count, file location, and file size.
.TP
.B \-\-clean
Removes all entries from the log file.
.\"
.\" --------------------------------------------------------------------
.SS get
.B get get
.PP
Displays all application information (version, introduction, license,
GitHub URL).
.TP
.B \-\-intro
Displays the one-line introduction.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Displays the version string (equivalent to
.BR "get version" ).
.TP
.B \-\-license
Displays the SPDX license identifier.
.TP
.B \-\-github
Displays the GitHub repository URL.
.\"
.\" --------------------------------------------------------------------
.SS version
.B get version
.PP
Prints the version string and exits.
.\"
.\" --------------------------------------------------------------------
.SS isok
.B get isok
.PP
Verifies that the current configuration is ready for use.
Checks that the API key, URL, and model are all set, then sends a
lightweight probe request to the LLM endpoint.
Exits with code 0 on success, 1 on failure.
.\"
.\" --------------------------------------------------------------------
.SS help
.B get help
.PP
Displays comprehensive usage help.
Also triggered by
.B \-\-help
and
.BR \-h .
.\"
.\" ====================================================================
.SH QUERY FLAGS
Per-invocation flags that override the persisted configuration for a
single query.
These flags are placed after the query string.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-cache
Bypass the cache for this query.
.TP
.B \-\-cache
Force cache lookup and storage for this query.
.TP
.B \-\-manual\-confirm
Prompt for confirmation before executing each generated command.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-manual\-confirm
Skip the confirmation prompt.
.TP
.B \-\-double\-check
Enable the second LLM safety review.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-double\-check
Skip the second LLM safety review.
.TP
.B \-\-instance
Use single-call instance mode; output is always shown directly.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-instance
Use multi-round agent mode (the default).
.TP
.B \-\-hide\-process
Suppress intermediate output (progress, commands, round markers).
.TP
.B \-\-no\-hide\-process
Show intermediate output.
.TP
.B \-\-vivid
Enable vivid output mode (colours, animated spinners, external
rendering via bat/mdcat).
.TP
.B \-\-no\-vivid
Use plain-text output mode (no colours or animations).
.TP
.BI \-\-model " name"
Override the LLM model for this query.
.TP
.BI \-\-timeout " seconds"
Override the request timeout for this query.
.\"
.\" ====================================================================
.SH SET OPTIONS
The following options can be configured with
.BR "get set" .
Integer options accept
.B false
to disable the feature entirely (equivalent to 0).
An empty value resets the option to its default or clears the stored
value for string options.
.TP
.BI "key " string
LLM API key.
Stored using platform-specific secure storage (Linux: file permissions
0600; Windows: DPAPI).
Default: empty.
.TP
.BI "url " URL
LLM API endpoint URL (OpenAI-compatible).
Default:
.IR https://api.poe.com/v1 .
.TP
.BI "model " string
LLM model name.
Default:
.IR gpt\-5.3\-codex .
.TP
.BI "manual\-confirm " bool
Whether to require manual confirmation before executing generated
commands.
Default:
.IR false .
.TP
.BI "double\-check " bool
Whether to invoke the model for a second safety review of each
generated command.
Default:
.IR true .
.TP
.BI "instance " bool
Whether to use single-call instance mode.
When
.IR false ,
the multi-round agent loop is used.
Default:
.IR false .
.TP
.BI "timeout " "integer | false"
Timeout for a single API request, in seconds.
Default:
.IR 300 .
.TP
.BI "max\-token " "integer | false"
Maximum token consumption per request.
Default:
.IR 20480 .
.TP
.BI "max\-rounds " "integer | false"
Maximum number of loop rounds in agent mode.
When the cap is reached the model is forced to produce a final answer.
Has no effect in instance mode.
Default:
.IR 3 .
.TP
.BI "command\-pattern " regex
Regex pattern matching forbidden commands; execution is rejected if the
generated command matches.
When set to a custom value,
.B get
checks whether the pattern adequately covers common dangerous commands
and emits a warning if not.
Default: built-in blocklist (see
.BR SAFETY ).
.TP
.BI "system\-prompt " string
Custom system prompt appended to the LLM context.
Default: empty.
.TP
.BI "shell " string
The shell used to execute commands.
Default:
.I powershell
on Windows;
.I bash
on Linux.
.TP
.BI "log " bool
Whether to log each request and execution.
Default:
.IR true .
.TP
.BI "hide\-process " bool
Whether to hide intermediate steps and only output the final result.
Default:
.IR false .
.TP
.BI "cache " bool
Whether to enable response caching.
Default:
.IR true .
.TP
.BI "cache\-expiry " "integer | false"
Number of days before a cache entry expires.
Default:
.IR 30 .
.TP
.BI "cache\-max\-entries " "integer | false"
Maximum number of entries retained in the cache.
Default:
.IR 1000 .
.TP
.BI "log\-max\-entries " "integer | false"
Maximum number of entries retained in the log.
Default:
.IR 1000 .
.TP
.BI "vivid " bool
Whether to use vivid output mode.
See
.BR "OUTPUT STYLES" .
Default:
.IR true .
.TP
.BI "external\-display " bool
Whether to use
.BR bat (1)
and
.BR mdcat (1)
for syntax-highlighted and Markdown output rendering in vivid mode.
Has no effect in plain mode.
Default:
.IR true .
.\"
.\" ====================================================================
.SH AGENT MODE PROTOCOL
In agent mode (the default, used when
.B instance
is
.IR false )
.B get
engages in a multi-round conversation with the LLM.
In each round the model emits a response that must follow one of four
formats:
.TP
.B "CONTINUE — intermediate command"
A command wrapped in a
.B sh
code fence, followed by
.BR "<!-- CONTINUE -->" .
The command is executed and its output is fed back to the model for
the next round.
Used when the model needs preliminary information before producing a
final answer.
.TP
.B "FINAL — terminal command with direct output"
A command wrapped in a
.B sh
code fence, followed by
.B "<!-- FINAL -->"
(or no marker; FINAL is the default when a code block is present).
The command is executed and its raw output is shown directly to the
user.
This terminates the loop.
.TP
.B "INTERPRET — terminal command with summarised output"
A command wrapped in a
.B sh
code fence, followed by
.BR "<!-- INTERPRET -->" .
The command is executed and its output is sent back to the model,
which produces a human-readable summary.
This terminates the loop.
Used sparingly, only when raw output genuinely needs explanation.
.TP
.B "ANSWER — direct text response"
No code block at all; the model's plain-text response is shown to the
user.
Used when no shell command can satisfy the query.
This terminates the loop.
.PP
The loop is bounded by
.B max\-rounds
(default 3).
When the final round is reached, any
.B "<!-- CONTINUE -->"
marker is forcibly converted to
.B "<!-- FINAL -->"
so that the run always terminates with a concrete answer.
Every intermediate and final command passes through the full safety
pipeline before execution.
.\"
.\" ====================================================================
.SH SAFETY
.B get
is designed to perform read-only operations only.
The LLM is prompted with strict read-only constraints, and every
generated command — intermediate or final — undergoes multiple layers
of validation before execution:
.TP
.B 1. Forbidden-command pattern
A regex matcher rejects commands matching the configured
.B command\-pattern
before they can execute.
When no custom pattern is set, the built-in blocklist is used.
.IP
The built-in blocklist targets (with word boundaries):
.BR rm ,
.BR rmdir ,
.BR del ,
.BR erase ,
.BR mv ,
.BR move ,
.BR cp ,
.BR copy ,
.BR mkdir ,
.BR touch ,
.BR chmod ,
.BR chown ,
.BR chgrp ,
.BR mkfs ,
.BR dd ,
.BR fdisk ,
.BR kill ,
.BR killall ,
.BR pkill ,
.BR shutdown ,
.BR reboot ,
.BR halt ,
.BR poweroff ,
.BR passwd ,
.BR useradd ,
.BR userdel ,
.BR usermod ,
.BR groupadd ,
.BR groupdel ,
.BR Set\-Content ,
.BR New\-Item ,
.BR Remove\-Item ,
.BR Move\-Item ,
.BR Rename\-Item ,
.BR Clear\-Content ,
and
.BR Add\-Content .
.TP
.B 2. Double-check
(Default: enabled.)
A second LLM safety review of each generated command.
The reviewer model assesses whether the command is strictly read-only
and safe, and may revise the command or reject it outright by
responding with the single word
.BR UNSAFE .
.TP
.B 3. Manual confirmation
Optional interactive y/N prompt via the
.B manual\-confirm
setting.
When enabled, confirmation is requested before every command
execution, including intermediate agent-mode commands.
.\"
.\" ====================================================================
.SH MODEL STRENGTH
.B get
executes shell commands generated by the LLM on your device.
A sufficiently capable model is the foundation of safety.
At startup,
.B get
checks the configured model name against a built-in whitelist of known
high-performance model families and displays a warning if the model is
not recognised or belongs to a weak variant.
.PP
Recognised strong families and their minimum versions:
.TP
.B GPT / CodeX
version >= 5 (e.g.\&
.IR gpt\-5.3\-codex ).
.TP
.B Claude
.I Opus
or
.I Sonnet
version >= 3.5, or any Claude model with version >= 3.7.
.TP
.B Gemini
version >= 3.
.TP
.B Grok
version >= 4.
.TP
.B MiniMax
version >= 2.7.
.TP
.B GLM / ChatGLM
version >= 4.7.
.TP
.B DeepSeek
full variants (non-distilled).
.TP
.B OpenAI o-series
version >= 3.
.PP
Reduced-capability variants containing keywords such as
.BR mini ,
.BR nano ,
.BR lite ,
.BR small ,
.BR fast ,
.BR flash ,
.BR haiku ,
.BR light ,
.BR tiny ,
.BR micro ,
or
.B instant
are always treated as weak.
Unsupported families
.RB ( Doubao ,
.BR Qwen ,
.BR Ernie / Wenxin ,
.BR Hunyuan ,
.BR Spark ,
.BR Baichuan ,
.BR Yi )
are explicitly blocked from the whitelist.
Model names are normalised before comparison — case differences and
underscores vs hyphens are handled transparently
.RB ( Claude_Opus_4.6
and
.B claude\-opus\-4.6
are equivalent).
The warning is advisory and does not block execution.
.\"
.\" ====================================================================
.SH OUTPUT STYLES
.B get
supports two output styles, selected by the
.B vivid
boolean setting:
.TP
.B plain (vivid = false)
Plain text on a monochrome terminal: no colours, no animations, no
external rendering.
Section boundaries are separated by blank lines.
Spinners are replaced with dotted progress indicators.
.TP
.B vivid (vivid = true, default)
ANSI colours, animated Braille-dot spinners during long-running
requests, bold section headers, and optional rendering through
.BR bat (1)
(for syntax-highlighted command output and help text) and
.BR mdcat (1)
(for Markdown-formatted interpreted results).
On Windows,
.B get
enables virtual terminal processing automatically.
.PP
When
.B external\-display
is enabled (default) and vivid mode is active, the bundled
.BR bat (1)
and
.BR mdcat (1)
binaries are used for rendering.
If the required binaries are not found in the bundled
.I bin/
directory,
.B get
falls back to its built-in colouriser and emits a warning listing the
missing tools.
Setting
.B external\-display
to
.B true
while vivid mode is disabled produces a warning noting that the
setting has no effect in plain mode.
.\"
.\" ====================================================================
.SH CACHING
.B get
caches the final output of each query keyed by a hash of the query
text and execution context (working directory, shell, model, instance
mode, system prompt, command pattern, host OS, and CPU architecture).
When the same query is run under the same context, the cached entry is
used without issuing further API calls.
.PP
Before storing a new cache entry,
.B get
sends a lightweight LLM request to determine how the result should be
cached.
The model replies with one of three decisions:
.TP
.B RESULT
The output is stable (e.g.\& system version, project structure, static
configuration).
The final output is cached directly and returned on subsequent hits.
.TP
.B COMMAND
The command is reusable but the output is volatile (e.g.\& current
time, CPU usage, running processes).
Only the command is cached; on a hit it is re-executed to produce
fresh output.
All safety layers and logging still apply to the re-execution.
.TP
.B NOCACHE
Neither the command nor the output should be cached.
Used for context-dependent or ephemeral queries.
.PP
To bypass the cache for a single query, use the
.B \-\-no\-cache
flag:
.PP
.RS
.B get \(dqyour query\(dq \-\-no\-cache
.RE
.PP
Cache parameters can be tuned with
.BR "get set cache\-expiry" ,
.BR "get set cache\-max\-entries" ,
and
.BR "get set cache" .
See
.B SET OPTIONS
for details.
.\"
.\" ====================================================================
.SH LOGGING
.B get
logs each query execution (query text, generated command, exit code,
and output preview) to a local file.
In agent mode, each intermediate round is logged separately with a
.IR "(round N)"
suffix on the query text.
When the entry count exceeds the
.B log\-max\-entries
limit (unless disabled with
.BR false ),
the oldest entries are automatically removed.
.PP
Logging parameters can be tuned with
.B "get set log\-max\-entries"
and
.BR "get set log" .
.\"
.\" ====================================================================
.SH BUNDLED TOOLS
.B get
ships with several high-performance command-line tools in the
.I bin/
directory.
These tools are automatically available to generated commands via PATH
prepending.
.TP
.B rg
ripgrep \(em ultra-fast regex search in files.
.TP
.B fd
Fast file/directory finder.
.TP
.B sg
ast-grep \(em AST-level structural code search.
.TP
.B pmc
pack-my-code \(em code context packaging for LLM prompts.
.TP
.BR treepp " (Windows) / " tree " (Linux)"
tree++ (Windows) / classic Unix tree (Linux) \(em directory tree
listing.
.TP
.B tokei
Code statistics (lines of code by language).
.TP
.B lua
Lua 5.x interpreter for calculations and text processing.
.TP
.B bat
Syntax-highlighting cat replacement.
.TP
.B mdcat
Terminal Markdown renderer.
.PP
The LLM is made aware of these tools and prefers them when they fit
the task.
Write-mode flags on bundled tools (such as
.BR "pmc \-o" ,
.BR "pmc \-c" ,
.BR "tree \-o" ,
.BR "treepp /O" ,
or
.B "fd \-x"
with write commands) are explicitly forbidden in the prompt.
.\"
.\" ====================================================================
.SH SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS
.B get
requires a 64-bit platform (amd64 or arm64); this is enforced at
compile time.
At runtime a startup check looks for Windows 10+ or Linux kernel 6.0+
and emits an advisory warning if the requirement is not met.
.\"
.\" ====================================================================
.SH STATIC BUILDS
To produce a fully statically linked binary (no dynamic library
dependencies), build with the
.B staticBuild
flag.
This requires static OpenSSL libraries to be available on the system:
.PP
.RS
.B nim c \-d:release \-d:staticBuild src/get.nim
.RE
.\"
.\" ====================================================================
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B GET_TEST_KEY
API key used by the test suite for live LLM connectivity tests.
.TP
.B GET_TEST_URL
API endpoint URL used by the test suite.
.TP
.B GET_TEST_MODEL
Model name used by the test suite.
.PP
These variables are only relevant when running the test suite; they
are not used during normal operation.
.\"
.\" ====================================================================
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/get/config.json
Configuration file (Linux).
.TP
.I ~/.config/get/key
API key storage file (Linux, mode 0600).
.TP
.I ~/.config/get/get.log
Append-only execution log (Linux).
.TP
.I ~/.config/get/cache.json
Response cache file (Linux).
.TP
.I %APPDATA%/get/config.json
Configuration file (Windows).
.TP
.I %APPDATA%/get/key
API key storage file (Windows, DPAPI-encrypted).
.TP
.I %APPDATA%/get/get.log
Append-only execution log (Windows).
.TP
.I %APPDATA%/get/cache.json
Response cache file (Windows).
.TP
.IR <exe>/bin/ " or " <exe>/src/bin/
Bundled binary tools directory.
The production layout
.RI ( <exe>/bin/ )
is checked first, then the development layout
.RI ( <exe>/src/bin/ ).
.\"
.\" ====================================================================
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Successful completion.
.TP
.B 1
Configuration error, LLM communication failure, safety check
rejection, or general error.
.TP
.B 130
Interrupted by Ctrl+C (SIGINT).
.TP
.I N
When a generated command exits with a non-zero code, that code is
propagated as the exit status of
.BR get .
.\"
.\" ====================================================================
.SH EXAMPLES
Retrieve system version information:
.PP
.RS
.B get \(dqsystem version\(dq
.RE
.PP
List code files in the current directory:
.PP
.RS
.B get \(dqcode in the directory\(dq
.RE
.PP
Fetch information from a URL:
.PP
.RS
.B get \(dqthe latest get version at https://github.com/Water\-Run/get\(dq
.RE
.PP
Bypass the cache for a single query:
.PP
.RS
.B get \(dqdisk usage\(dq \-\-no\-cache
.RE
.PP
Override the model and enable vivid output for a single query:
.PP
.RS
.B get \(dqlist files\(dq \-\-model gpt\-5.3\-codex \-\-vivid
.RE
.PP
Force instance (single-call) mode:
.PP
.RS
.B get \(dqsystem uptime\(dq \-\-instance
.RE
.PP
Configure the API key:
.PP
.RS
.B get set key sk\-your\-api\-key
.RE
.PP
Configure the API endpoint:
.PP
.RS
.B get set url https://api.openai.com/v1
.RE
.PP
Unset the API key:
.PP
.RS
.B get set key
.RE
.PP
Disable the request timeout:
.PP
.RS
.B get set timeout false
.RE
.PP
Increase the agent-mode round budget:
.PP
.RS
.B get set max\-rounds 5
.RE
.PP
Switch to plain output mode:
.PP
.RS
.B get set vivid false
.RE
.PP
View a single configuration option:
.PP
.RS
.B get config \-\-model
.RE
.PP
Reset all configuration to defaults:
.PP
.RS
.B get config \-\-reset
.RE
.PP
Show cache status including per-mode entry counts:
.PP
.RS
.B get cache
.RE
.PP
Clear the cache:
.PP
.RS
.B get cache \-\-clean
.RE
.PP
Remove a specific cached query:
.PP
.RS
.B get cache \-\-unset \(dqsystem version\(dq
.RE
.PP
Clear the log:
.PP
.RS
.B get log \-\-clean
.RE
.PP
Verify configuration readiness:
.PP
.RS
.B get isok
.RE
